v><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 80%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Teaches all core subjects; must demonstrate competency across the middle grades curriculum.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Pedagogical Planning and Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Designs and implements effective lessons in hybrid/project-based models; adapts for varied learning settings.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Classroom Management and Culture</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Establishes a positive, inclusive learning environment both in-person and online; reinforces school values.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Differentiation and Inclusive Practices</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Adapts instruction for diverse learners, including academic, social, and emotional needs.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Assessment and Data-Driven Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Continuously tracks progress, uses data to inform instruction and communicate learning outcomes.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Curriculum Development and Standards Alignment</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Adapts and aligns curriculum to state/charter standards, project-based themes.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Technology-Enhanced Instruction</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Integrates online learning platforms for hybrid teaching and engagement; key for remote weeks.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Communication and Family Engagement</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Maintains regular, proactive communication with students'' families and school community.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Collaboration and Professionalism</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 5</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 50%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 7</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 70%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Engages in staff collaboration, PD, and school-wide initiatives; contributes to positive professional culture.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Student SEL and Wellbeing</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Supports students'' social and emotional growth; creates an affirming learning environment.</div></div><div class="req-row"><div class="req-name">Culturally Responsive Teaching</div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Minimum: 4</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill min" style="width: 40%;"></div></div></div><div class="level"><div class="lvl-label">Target: 6</div><div class="meter"><div class="fill target" style="width: 60%;"></div></div></div><div class="just">Builds relationships with students/families from diverse backgrounds; fosters respect and inclusion.</div></div></div></div></div><div class="card ana"><h2>Detailed Analysis</h2><div class="section"><div><strong>Role Snapshot:</strong><ul><li>Hybrid middle school teaching for grades 6-8</li><li>Teaches all core academic subjects</li><li>Project-based and student-centered focus</li><li>Innovative, inclusive charter school</li><li>Start: August 2024; alternating in-person and remote weeks</li></ul></div><div><strong>Core Responsibilities:</strong><ul><li>Design and deliver engaging hybrid lessons</li><li>Assess and report student progress across subjects</li><li>Integrate technology in remote and in-person settings</li><li>Actively participate in professional development</li><li>Collaborate with teachers, staff, and coaches</li><li>Foster a positive, respectful classroom culture</li></ul></div><div><strong>Student Needs & Differentiation:</strong><ul><li>Adapt instruction for diverse learning needs</li><li>Support students'' social and emotional development</li><li>Incorporate SEL and inclusive practices</li><li>Use flexible strategies for academic support</li></ul></div><div><strong>Collaboration & Communication:</strong><ul><li>Sustained family communication</li><li>Engagement in professional learning communities</li><li>Active school community participation</li></ul></div><div><strong>Technology Expectations:</strong><ul><li>Use of Google Classroom, Zoom, & online tools</li><li>Facilitate hybrid/blended learning</li><li>Utilize technology for engagement and assessment</li></ul></div><div><strong>Other Notes:</strong><ul><li>Small class sizes (max 20 students)</li><li>Inclusive and growth-oriented environment</li><li>2+ years teaching experience preferred</li><li>Certification preferred but not strictly required</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>', N'{
