agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Emily is an outstanding K2 technology and STEM leader, as proven by metrics and awards. The strongest negative is her lack of direct upper elementary science experience and NGSS curriculum record, which increases onboarding and ramp-up costs for Crestviews foundational 25 science launch.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">This agent places the greatest short-term weight on the absence of demonstrated grades 25 science content expertise and the cost/risk of needing to provide extensive mentoring.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-Sunny"><div class="agent-name">Sunny Sam</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span> <span class="score-badge score-orange">77.00%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-positive">+7.17%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Emilys team-building, creativity, and positive energy make her a long-term jackpot for collaborative culture, tech integration, and innovationhallmarks for Crestviews founding school spirit. Still, she will require upfront science PD and mentoring to fulfill independent grades 25 science leadership, but her adaptability and drive suggest shell bridge gaps quickly.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">My score is higher than the team average because I value Emilys future potential, culture impact, and the outsized return on investing in her growthbut acknowledge that she is not yet a turnkey science lead.</span></div></div></div></section><section class="section" id="next-steps"><div class="section-header">Recommended Next Steps</div><div class="section-body next-steps"><div class="recommendation">Proceed with interview if the school is prepared to invest in science content professional development; otherwise, prioritize a candidate with immediate grades 25 science expertise.</div><div class="footnote">Note: Recommendations are based on the overall match and agent inputs. Adjust as needed with additional context or updated information.</div></div></section></main></body></html>', N'', N'a504e78d-4e7a-4fc7-baba-562528b506e3', N'9cba86dd-c7e4-41d5-aef1-830dc82a176f', N'9294366f-5030-4993-a303-77aedc9d0231', 1, 1)
