rates outstanding skill as a technology-oriented, recognized K2 teacher, with leadership in curriculum, team-building, and measurable positive impact. However, for Harmony Ridge''s Middle School role, her experience is short of the 7+ years and entirely in early childhood, her credential is from Illinois (not California), and she does not offer documented grades 68, multi-content, or Spanish-speaking proficiency. All expert reviewers note that her proven value in K2 or tech-integration roles does not extend to the technical requirements, classroom management demands, or credential/licensure specifications for this post, resulting in high onboarding/training costs and delayed value for the district in this targeted role.</div></div></section><section class="section" id="positives"><div class="section-header">Strengths (Match Positives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Demonstrated measurable impact in K2 technology and curriculum innovation</li><li>Recognized for collaborative leadership, including team and family engagement</li><li>Award-winning teaching (multiple recognitions at current school)</li><li>High adaptation to growth and new instructional technology</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="negatives"><div class="section-header">Gaps or Risks (Match Negatives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>No California credential (Illinois only listed)</li><li>Only five years teaching experience (less than required 7+)</li><li>No grades 68 or multi-subject content expertise in evidence</li><li>No Spanish proficiency or bilingual experience documented</li><li>Potentially high onboarding and retraining costs for middle school, multi-content role</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="agents"><div class="section-header">Agent Evaluations</div><div class="section-body"><div class="agent" id="agent-taylor-grant"><div class="agent-name">Taylor Grant</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-yellow">43.80%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-positive">+4.02%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Emily is an innovative, team-building K2 educator with exceptional results in technology and curriculum. For Harmony Ridge''s 68, multi-content, CA-credentialed, Spanish-preferred opening, credential and subject-matter gaps outweigh her distinct early grade strengths. She has long-term value within primary grades/specialist posts, but is not strategically suited to this posting.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Taylor values Emily''s above-average innovation and team leadership, weighting creativity and long-range potential, hence landing slightly above the overall composite.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-jordan-lee"><div class="agent-name">Jordan Lee</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-yellow">36.10%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-3.68%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Emily has measurable K2 success in technology integration, curriculum design, and engagement, but lacks every major technical requirement (years, grade, credential, Spanish, core-content mastery) for the Harmony Ridge post. Peer consensus and data-driven mismatch justify this low rating.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Jordan focuses strictly on objective technical and credential alignment, scoring lower due to complete absence of directly transferable core qualification.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-sunny-sam"><div class="agent-name">Sunny Sam</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-yellow">39.45%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-0.33%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Emily''s culture-building, positive energy, and school innovation would be a huge asset in early years or tech integration, but for 68 multi-content teaching, credential, grade, and subject alignment are major barriers. Her value for this specific role is outpaced by the credentialed/experienced need.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Sam weights culture and potential highly, but agrees the current technical fit for this position is very low. Small differential above consensus reflects enduring appreciation of team/culture impact.</span></div></div></div></section><section class="section" id="next-steps"><div class="section-header">Recommended Next Steps</div><div class="section-body next-steps"><div class="recommendation">Do not proceed to interviewseek candidate for K2 or technology integration roles instead.</div><div class="footnote">Note: Recommendations are based on the overall match and agent inputs. Adjust as needed with additional context or updated information.</div></div></section></main></body></html>', N'', N'a504e78d-4e7a-4fc7-baba-562528b506e3', N'31951735-d8e3-4f4a-961f-84628e991dc3', N'044b8fb0-5960-487c-a4d3-f932e6976ee4', 3, 1)
