community partnership skills</li><li>Proven commitment to team culture, morale, and professional growth</li><li>Very low risk for turnover; reliable, positive long-term contributor</li><li>Clear evidence of creative lesson planning and learning innovation</li><li>Track record of volunteerism, event leadership, and positive collaboration</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="negatives"><div class="section-header">Gaps or Risks (Match Negatives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>No recent experience in a formal (grades 6-8) middle school classroom</li><li>Lacks state teaching certification and advanced hybrid/LMS tech skills</li><li>May require moderate onboarding and professional development for adolescent group management</li><li>Not immediately ready for hybrid/project-based routines used at this school</li><li>Initial technology ramp-up will require dedicated mentorship or PD</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="agents"><div class="section-header">Agent Evaluations</div><div class="section-body"><div class="agent" id="agent-1"><div class="agent-name">Taylor Grant</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-green">81.25%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-0.45%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Jane matches especially well for culture, long-term commitment, and instructional design, but lacks plug-and-play readiness for middle school team routines and hybrid/edtech demands. Her reliability, community spirit, and quick cultural adaptation are major plusses. With targeted onboarding, shes a strong investment and will likely thrive, but not an immediate technical match.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Taylor focuses more heavily on the cost/risk of short-term onboarding and hybrid MS adaptation; slight negative difference reflects this pragmatic weighting despite strong overall fit.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-2"><div class="agent-name">Jordan Lee</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-green">80.45%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-1.25%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Janes years of K-12 curriculum design, classroom management, and family communication ensure strong baseline fit, and her adaptability suggests rapid growth with school support. Her persistent gaps in middle school adolescent management and hybrid learning tools mean onboarding costs, but her success in diverse settings and culture-building is a net plus.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Jordan puts greater analytic emphasis on measurable skill gaps and integration costs in MS/hybrid teaching, lowering score slightly versus overall consensus.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-3"><div class="agent-name">Sunny Sam</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-green">83.40%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-positive">+1.70%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Janes warmth, adaptability, and history of inspiring and engaging families and staff make her ideal for school culture building. She lacks technical skills for immediate hybrid middle school transition, yet her learning agility and positive influence offset technical gaps. With supportive PD, her spark will quickly shine across campus.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-to