);box-shadow: var(--shadow);overflow: hidden;} .section-header {padding: 14px 16px;background: var(--card);border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);font-weight: 700;font-size: 15px;letter-spacing: .2px;} .section-body {padding: 16px;font-size: 15px;} .muted { color: var(--muted); } .list {display:grid; gap: 8px; padding-left: 18px; margin: 0;} .list li { margin-left: 6px; } /* Agents */ #agents .agent {border: 1px solid var(--border);border-radius: 8px;padding: 14px;background: #fff;margin-bottom: 12px;} .agent .agent-name {font-weight: 700;margin-bottom: 6px;} .agent .agent-match-line {display:flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items:center; gap: 8px;margin-bottom: 8px;} .diff {display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;min-width: 56px;padding: 4px 8px;border-radius: 999px;font-weight: 600;font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;border: 1px solid transparent;background: var(--neutral-bg);color: var(--neutral);} .diff-positive { color: var(--green); background: var(--green-bg); border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--green) 20%, transparent); } .diff-negative { color: var(--red); background: var(--red-bg); border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--red) 20%, transparent); } .diff-neutral { color: var(--neutral); background: var(--neutral-bg); } .agent .label { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; margin-right: 6px; } .agent .text { white-space: pre-wrap; } /* Next steps */ .next-steps .recommendation {font-weight: 700;padding: 8px 10px;background: var(--card);border: 1px solid var(--border);border-radius: 8px;display:inline-block;margin-bottom: 10px;} .questions { padding-left: 18px; margin: 0; display: grid; gap: 8px; } .footnote { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; margin-top: 10px; } /* Responsiveness */ @media (min-width: 720px){ header.summary {grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;align-items: center;} .summary-top { justify-content: flex-start; gap: 18px; } .candidate { margin-left: 6px; } } /* Print */ @media print { .container { max-width: 100%; margin:0; padding:0 8mm; } .section, header.summary { box-shadow: none; } }</style></head><body><main class="container"><header class="summary"><div class="summary-top"><div class="title-line"><div class="position">Middle School Teacher</div><div class="org">Harmony Ridge Middle School</div></div><div class="candidate">Candidate: Samantha R. Lopez</div></div><div class="summary-score"><span class="score-badge score-orange">64.6%</span></div></header><section class="section" id="analysis"><div class="section-header">Analysis</div><div class="section-body"><div class="text">Samantha R. Lopez is an experienced, dedicated high school English/Theatre teacher with five years classroom experience, advanced Spanish proficiency, a special education endorsement, and a proven track record of club leadership and student impactstrongly aligning her with Harmony Ridges inclusive, collaborative, and bilingual-focused teaching vision. However, she does not hold a California credential (currently licensed in Illinois), has only five (not the required seven) years teaching, and her experience is limited to high school ELA/Theatre, not the full range of middle-level core subjects. While she is an exceptional cultural and school-climate fit with clear strengths in classroom management, SEL, and family engagement, her lack of state credential and mandated subject/experience breadth means she is a moderate technical match who would require significant investment in professional development and licensure to fully meet this postings needs. All agents converge on this assessment and rating.</div></div></section><section class="section" id="positives"><div class="section-header">Strengths (Match Positives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Documented strengths in classroom management, curriculum development, and student engagement</li><li>Bilingual: ACTFL Advanced High Spanish proficiency</li><li>Special Education (LBS1) endorsement; strong IEP/504 practice</li><li>Leadership in student clubs (e.g. art club, honor society); proven mentorship and community building</li><li>Highly collaborative, inclusive, and culturally responsive educator</li><li>Clear commitment to family partnership and positive school climate</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="negatives"><div class="section-header">Gaps or Risks (Match Negatives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Does not have a California teaching credential (only Illinois PEL)</li><li>Five years experienceshort of the required 7+ years</li><li>No documented multi-subject or middle school level math/science/social studies instruction</li><li>Lack of direct evidence for data-driven, standards-based multi-subject assessment at the middle level</li><li>Would require significant investment in credentialing, training, or subject expansion</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="agents"><div class="section-header">Agent Evaluations</div><div class="section-body"><div class="agent" id="agent-TaylorGrant"><div class="agent-name">Taylor Grant</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-orange">64.66%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-neutral">0.06%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Samantha''s cultural, linguistic, and pedagogical alignment to Harmony Ridge is strong; she shines in collaboration, inclusivity, parental engagement, and club leadership. However, she does not hold a California credential, lacks the required years of experience and subject breadth for a multi-subject middle school role, and would need time and investment to close those gaps. Her warmth and proven record argue for long-term value, but immediate technical fit falls just short of the jobs requirements.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">The agent score is essentially identical to the overall, demonstrating total agreement on the balance of cultural strengths and technical/credential limitations.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-JordanLee"><div class="agent-name">Jordan Lee</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-orange">64.7%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-positive">0.10%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Samanthas record is replete with collaboration, Spanish fluency, special education endorsement, and measurable club-growth and inclusion results that match strongly with what Harmony Ridge seeks in ethos and school culture. She lacks the essential licensure and specific multi-subject/middle school teaching experience required, so her candidacy falls short on strict compliance. With support for credentialing and subject expansion, she would be a clear long-term asset.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">The agent rating is negligibly above the overall score, due to an extra emphasis on Samanthas measurable achievement and long-term potential for team cohesion.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-SunnySam"><div class="agent-name">Sunny Sam</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-orange">64.46%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-0.14%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Samantha sparkles as a team- and student-builder, bringing energy, inclusion, and Spanish skills that would lift any campus. Her documented impact and warmth make her a cultural match. The notable gapsstate credential, experience threshold, and multi-subject evidencepreclude her from an immediate fit, but not from being an investment-worthy educator for a more flexible or upskilling-ready team.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">This slightly lower match reflects extra weight on the risk of non-compliance and cost/timing of credential upskilling. Strengths in culture are acknowledged, but not enough to offset missing job essentials.</span></div></div></div></section><section class="section" id="next-steps"><div class="section-header">Recommended Next Steps</div><div class="section-body next-steps"><div class="recommendation">Move forward with candidates who hold California credentials and documented multi-subject middle school experience for this particular opening. Consider Samantha for other roles that more closely align with her background, or invest in a longer onboarding process if her cultural fit is prioritized over technical compliance.</div><div class="footnote">Note: Recommendations are based on the overall match and agent inputs. Adjust as needed with additional context or updated information.</div></div></section></main></body></html>', N'', N'7b2eac48-1530-4897-96c1-bf9810db8c98', N'31951735-d8e3-4f4a-961f-84628e991dc3', N'a267e83f-7888-47ec-8586-53b2a4ee74ca', 3, 4)
