 Department</div><div class="org">Lincoln Heights High School</div></div><div class="candidate">Candidate: Samantha R. Lopez</div></div><div class="summary-score"><span class="score-badge score-red">31.43%</span></div></header><section class="section" id="analysis"><div class="section-header">Analysis</div><div class="section-body"><div class="text">All three agents independently agree that while Samantha R. Lopez demonstrates significant skill as a classroom teacher, team player, and arts/program leader, she lacks the mathematics-specific expertise, AP-level teaching, and math department leadership required for this role. The consensus is that the core outcomesadvanced math instruction, department stewardship, and mentoring math teacherswould not be possible based on her current profile. Her general strengths do not address the non-negotiable competencies for this specialist leadership post.</div></div></section><section class="section" id="positives"><div class="section-header">Strengths (Match Positives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Strong classroom management and student engagement skills</li><li>Leadership and experience in curriculum development and extracurricular programs</li><li>Commitment to inclusion, diversity, and equity in the classroom</li><li>Positive attitude, resilience, and collaboration with staff</li><li>Recognition for teaching excellence and innovation</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="negatives"><div class="section-header">Gaps or Risks (Match Negatives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>No evidence of advanced or AP mathematics teaching experience</li><li>No verified mathematics content knowledge or certifications</li><li>Lack of math department leadership or mentoring of math teachers</li><li>No measurable math-student outcomes or results</li><li>Training requirements would be high; risks to department continuity and performance</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="agents"><div class="section-header">Agent Evaluations</div><div class="section-body"><div class="agent" id="agent-1"><div class="agent-name">Taylor Grant</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-red">31.20%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-0.23%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Taylor emphasized Samantha''s robust leadership in general education and the arts but concludedfollowing close consensus and final calibrationthat the absence of mathematics instructional, AP-level, and leadership credentials outweighed her general strengths. Final adjustment brought the score below her initial evaluations to reflect the consensus.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Taylor''s score aligns nearly exactly with the overall rated value, showing strong adoption of the consensus that subject-specific leadership is the decisive factor.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-2"><div class="agent-name">Jordan Lee</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-red">31.00%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-0.43%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Jordan adopted the most conservative view, matching the consensus on the non-negotiable failure to meet the core job requirements: advanced/high school math teaching and mentoring math teachers. All of Samantha''s notable skills are general, not mathematics-specific or leadership focused.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Jordan''s rating is just below the group average, strengthening the consensus that even outstanding overall educators cannot bridge a total content and leadership gap for this role.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-3"><div class="agent-name">Sunny Sam</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-red">32.10%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-positive">+0.67%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Sunny Sam prioritized Samantha&rsquo;s positive impact on school culture and inclusion, but after reviewing peer scores, moved closer to consensus on the decisive lack of technical qualifications. Even exceptional soft skills can''t compensate for missing specialized leadership and AP math experience.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Sunny''s rating is slightly above the consensus, reflecting a little more weight assigned to general skills and positive team fit, though still rating the candidate as clearly noncompetitive for this specialized post.</span></div></div></div></section><section class="section" id="next-steps"><div class="section-header">Recommended Next Steps</div><div class="section-body next-steps"><div class="recommendation">Do not advance candidate to next interview round for this role; encourage application to more closely-matched teaching or extracurricular posts.</div><div class="footnote">Note: Recommendations are based on the overall match and agent inputs. Adjust as needed with additional context or updated information.</div></div></section></main></body></html>', N'', N'7b2eac48-1530-4897-96c1-bf9810db8c98', N'd0617c28-c7db-4f51-a14e-2035dad9f354', N'a9dd7c7d-ff03-4937-a855-e1ecb9e01eda', 4, 4)
