-score"><span class="score-badge score-orange">70.2%</span></div></header><section class="section" id="analysis"><div class="section-header">Analysis</div><div class="section-body"><div class="text">Jessica Ramirez is an innovative, tech-forward, and collaborative educator with a strong record in technology integration, culture-building, and professional development. She fits Crestview Academy''s vision for a creative, adaptive founding team, but has a substantial skills gap in teaching upper-elementary science, designing NGSS-aligned lessons, and leading inquiry-based labs. Her upside is high for long-term strategic staff development, though she requires significant onboarding to meet independent day-one science content needs.</div></div></section><section class="section" id="positives"><div class="section-header">Strengths (Match Positives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Outstanding EdTech integration skills (Nearpod, Seesaw, Google, etc.)</li><li>Strong team-builder and peer instructional coach</li><li>Demonstrated success with family engagement and positive classroom culture</li><li>Adaptable, growth-minded, and innovative</li><li>Experience in curriculum creation for early childhood education</li><li>Certified in Texas (EC6), with relevant EdTech credentials</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="negatives"><div class="section-header">Gaps or Risks (Match Negatives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Lack of direct upper-elementary (grades 25) science teaching experience</li><li>No documented science lab management or NGSS-aligned lesson delivery</li><li>Needs significant onboarding for independent science instruction</li><li>Majority of teaching background focused on Kindergarten/PreK</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="agents"><div class="section-header">Agent Evaluations</div><div class="section-body"><div class="agent" id="agent-taylor"><div class="agent-name">Taylor Grant</div><div clas