ss="summary-score"><span class="score-badge score-orange">63.42%</span></div></header><section class="section" id="analysis"><div class="section-header">Analysis</div><div class="section-body"><div class="text">Jessica Ramirez brings notable energy, digital teaching strength, and a collaborative mindset ideal for a tech-forward, project-based charter school. Her technology integration, family engagement, and coaching experience mark her as an instructional leader and PD role model. While her exclusive work in Pre-K/K creates a major content/age-level gap for immediate middle school deployment, she presents long-term developmental value for a growth-minded, mentor-rich environment ready to support her upskilling in grades 68 core teaching.</div></div></section><section class="section" id="positives"><div class="section-header">Strengths (Match Positives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Outstanding technology integration (Google Classroom, Nearpod, Seesaw, Zoom)</li><li>Quantifiable impact on student learning (15% increase in assessments at the K level)</li><li>Strong family and community engagement</li><li>Active professional development involvement and peer coaching</li><li>Certifications relevant to innovative/blended learning environments</li><li>Collaborative, uplifting team-builder</li><li>Growth mindset and willingness to pursue new methodology</li><li>Proven resilience and adaptability</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="negatives"><div class="section-header">Gaps or Risks (Match Negatives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>No documented teaching experience or content mastery for grades 68 core subject areas</li><li>Experience limited to early childhood (Pre-K/K)risk for classroom culture, management, and differentiation for pre-teens/adolescents</li><li>Steep learning curve for middle school curriculum, standards, and assessment practices</li><li>Requires significant investment in training, mentoring, and onboarding</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="agents"><div class="section-header">Agent Evaluations</div><div class="section-body"><div class="agent" id="agent-TaylorGrant"><div class="agent-name">Taylor Grant</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-orange">63.95%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-positive">+0.53%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Jessica is a technology leader and a positive culture-builder with strengths in professional development, lesson design, and peer mentoring. Her collaborative spirit and track record in upskilling make her a solid prospect for a school focused on growth and team cohesion. Persistent concerns remain regarding her lack of documented experience with middle grades content and standards, limiting her immediate classroom effectiveness for the advertised role.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Taylor''s slightly higher match reflects strong weighting on Jessicas collaborative/team-building and coaching abilities, slightly more than the consensusbut is largely in line with group sentiment acknowledging her growth potential despite content area gaps.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-JordanLee"><div class="agent-name">Jordan Lee</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-orange">62.80%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-0.62%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Jessica stands out in digital pedagogy, teamwork, and driving measurable results in early childhood education. She would excel in roles focused on instructional technology or team-based PD. However, the critical shortfall in verifiable middle grades subject expertise and direct adolescent classroom management means her match remains below those with subject-specific readiness for 68 core teaching.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Jordans match is marginally lower, reflecting a slightly more conservative stance on the requirement for plug-and-play subject-matter expertise. The reduction weighs the risk of transition and necessary investment more heavily than upside potential.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-SunnySam"><div class="agent-name">Sunny Sam</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-orange">65.50%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-positive">+2.08%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Jessicas optimism, resilience, and skill in inspiring others make her a strong asset for a culture-forward, growth-minded school. Her digital teaching acumen and mentorshipalong with willingness to learncould quickly create a ripple effect of innovation and morale-building. The content-area gap is acknowledged but weighed less heavily given her exceptional attitude and team uplifting ability.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Sunny places extra value on soft skills, cultural impact, and community-building, slightly elevating the score above the broader consensus. The higher difference reflects optimism about long-term team development outweighing short-term academic gaps.</span></div></div></div></section><section class="section" id="next-steps"><div class="section-header">Recommended Next Steps</div><div class="section-body next-steps"><div class="recommendation">Consider for a professional development-focused or technology specialist teaching role, or as a high-upside transition candidate. If immediate subject/grade-level deployment is required, prioritize candidates with direct middle grades core teaching experience. If Jessica is shortlisted, offer an interview focused on readiness to upskill, willingness to mentor, and strategies for adapting to middle school standards.</div><div class="footnote">Note: Recommendations are based on the overall match and agent inputs. Adjust as needed with additional context or updated information.</div></div></section></main></body></html>', N'', N'd4bc3c1d-08e0-4f78-9a9f-7631946e287a', N'f39f230e-1c1c-446a-bcb0-f40f8f48bdd4', N'9a35e66e-5ab8-400e-a391-88757bcfed18', 2, 5)
