</div><div class="section-body"><div class="text">Jessica Ramirez excels in early childhood education and technology integration, but she does not meet the required qualifications for Harmony Ridge''s Middle School Teacher role7+ years teaching grades 68, California credential, or multi-subject content area experience. Hiring her would involve high costs for training and licensing, with no guarantee of rapid success at the middle school level.</div></div></section><section class="section" id="positives"><div class="section-header">Strengths (Match Positives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Proven expertise in technology integration for classroom instruction</li><li>Strong curriculum design and innovation in Pre-K and Kindergarten</li><li>Skilled in building positive parent and staff relationships</li><li>Demonstrated results in student assessment and engagement for early grades</li><li>Certified in leading edtech programs (Seesaw, Google Classroom)</li><li>Supports and mentors peers on technology use</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="negatives"><div class="section-header">Gaps or Risks (Match Negatives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>No teaching experience in grades 68</li><li>Does not hold a California teaching credential or appropriate endorsement</li><li>Lacks 7+ years'' teaching experience as required</li><li>No evidence of multi-content teaching for middle school subjects</li><li>No documented Spanish proficiency</li><li>Would require excessive onboarding, credentialing, and training investment</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="agents"><div class="section-header">Agent Evaluations</div><div class="section-body"><div class="agent" id="agent-1"><div class="agent-name">Taylor Grant</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-red">37.1%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-0.5%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Jessica Ramirez is an emerging leader and innovator for early elementary settings, excelling in classroom technology and engagement, but she does not meet any of the minimum qualifications for middle school: 7+ years of relevant experience, a California teaching credential, or grades 68 subject expertise. Bringing her on would pose high costs for credentialing, support, and compliance. Her impact would be much better realized in K2 or technology integration roles.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Taylor Grant placed greater weight on hard requirements. The difference is minor and reflects a strong consensus, with Taylor slightly more conservative regarding fit due to compliance risk and onboarding costs.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-2"><div class="agent-name">Jordan Lee</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-red">37.5%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-negative">-0.1%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Jessica''s instructional and collaborative success in early childhood is clear, but all the mandatory requirements for this middle school roleyears, license, subject breadthare missing. Key outcomes in technology and K2 are not transferable to grades 68. The hiring risk is too high to justify proceeding.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Jordan Lees rating is nearly even with the overall; the difference comes from slightly more optimism about her potential after upskilling but acknowledges, in line with the consensus, that gaps are too significant.</span></div></div><div class="agent" id="agent-3"><div class="agent-name">Sunny Sam</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-red">38.2%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff diff-positive">+0.6%</span></div><div class="agent-justification"><span class="label">Justification:</span><span class="text">Jessica Ramirez brings positive energy, a growth mindset, and proven tech integration to early childhood education, making her a great fit for K2 or coaching. For the Harmony Ridge middle school opening, her lack of required experience, licensure, and subject-content breadth is prohibitive. Her value is highest in younger grade or innovation-focused contexts.</span></div><div class="agent-diff-reason" style="margin-top:6px;"><span class="label">Reason for difference from overall match:</span><span class="text">Sunny Sam gives a very slightly higher score to reflect Jessica''s standout qualities in team culture and tech, but acknowledges even excellence in these areas cannot meet non-negotiables for licensure and years at the middle school level.</span></div></div></div></section><section class="section" id="next-steps"><div class="section-header">Recommended Next Steps</div><div class="section-body next-steps"><div class="recommendation">Do not advance in process for this middle school role. Consider Jessica Ramirez for early elementary or technology integration/coach positions in the future.</div><div class="footnote">Note: Recommendations are based on the overall match and agent inputs. Adjust as needed with additional context or updated information.</div></div></section></main></body></html>', N'', N'd4bc3c1d-08e0-4f78-9a9f-7631946e287a', N'31951735-d8e3-4f4a-961f-84628e991dc3', N'7f26aa61-931e-4499-9732-a7fbb534cf91', 3, 5)
