or with quantifiable technology leadership, collaborative spirit, and proven impact in Pre-K/elementary settings. However, she has no grades 912, advanced mathematics, or secondary department leadership experiencerequirements that are essential for the Head of Mathematics Department at Lincoln Heights HS. All agent assessments converge on this mismatch: her strengths do not translate to this advanced content- and leadership-focused high school role.</div></div></section><section class="section" id="positives"><div class="section-header">Strengths (Match Positives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>Exemplary educator for early childhood/elementary grades</li><li>Innovative integration of technology in the classroom</li><li>Strong mentor in educational technology for peers</li><li>Consistent track record of student assessment gains</li><li>Recognized for building positive, student-centered classroom environments</li><li>Resilient, collaborative, and growth-minded attitude</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="negatives"><div class="section-header">Gaps or Risks (Match Negatives)</div><div class="section-body"><ul class="list"><li>No high school (grades 912) or AP math teaching experience</li><li>Lacks secondary math teacher certification</li><li>No departmental/secondary leadership or high school curriculum oversight</li><li>Does not meet critical subject-matter expertise in advanced math</li><li>Would require extensive training, upskilling, and certification changes</li><li>Transferability of elementary/tech skills to high school math is unproven</li></ul></div></section><section class="section" id="agents"><div class="section-header">Agent Evaluations</div><div class="section-body"><div class="agent" id="agent-TaylorGrant"><div class="agent-name">Taylor Grant</div><div class="agent-match-line"><span class="label">Match:</span><span class="score-badge score-red">20.60%</span><span class="label">? vs Overall:</span><span class="diff d