n with families and collaborative, cross-grade work are evidenced repeatedly. (5) She holds the required certifications at a higher level (PEL K-12, multiple endorsements). Pros: Plug-and-play expertise, very low ramp-up, proven ability to improve outcomes and manage transitions. Cons (budget/context): With 24 years of seniority, her salary expectations may be significantly higher than average for the position; she may also be slightly overqualified, which sometimes affects long-term retention at a less senior teaching role. However, her evident enthusiasm for broad impact (PD, mentoring, clubs, program building) increases the likelihood of her integrating well and contributing beyond baseline role expectations. Turnover risk appears very low, supporting long-term value.', N'This is the first fit analysis and thus sets the baseline. The match is high due to strong alignment with both hard and soft requirements, direct experience, certification, and proven impact. Value concerns primarily relate to compensation, not fit or capability.', 1, 1, N'5f43a9c1-d08e-44ff-895d-4974d5053f02', 33, CAST(87.70 AS Decimal(5, 2)))
GO
